## App Router Conventions

- **`page.tsx`** — defines the UI for a route segment. Always a Server Component unless `'use client'` is needed.
- **`layout.tsx`** — wraps children and persists across navigations. Use for navigation, sidebars, and shared UI.
- **`loading.tsx`** — shown while the page segment is loading (automatic Suspense boundary).
- **`error.tsx`** — must be a Client Component. Handles errors for a route segment.
- **`not-found.tsx`** — rendered when `notFound()` is called.

File naming uses lowercase with hyphens for directories: `app/user-profile/page.tsx`.

