## Testing Standards

### Unit Tests (Jest + React Testing Library)

```tsx
// __tests__/components/ContactCard.test.tsx
import { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';
import { ContactCard } from '@/components/ContactCard';

describe('ContactCard', () => {
  it('renders contact name and email', () => {
    render(
      <ContactCard
        name="Jane Doe"
        email="jane@example.com"
        message="Hello"
        createdAt="2024-01-01T00:00:00Z"
      />
    );

    expect(screen.getByText('Jane Doe')).toBeInTheDocument();
    expect(screen.getByText('jane@example.com')).toBeInTheDocument();
  });
});
```

### E2E Tests (Playwright)

```typescript
// e2e/contact-form.spec.ts
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test('submits contact form successfully', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/contact');
  await page.fill('[name="name"]', 'Jane Doe');
  await page.fill('[name="email"]', 'jane@example.com');
  await page.fill('[name="message"]', 'Hello world');
  await page.click('button[type="submit"]');
  await expect(page.getByText('Message sent')).toBeVisible();
});
```

**Rules:**
- Test behavior, not implementation (no testing internal state)
- Use `getByRole`, `getByText`, `getByLabelText` — avoid `getByTestId` unless no semantic selector exists
- Mock API calls in unit tests; use real API or MSW in E2E

---

## TypeScript Standards

- `strict: true` in `tsconfig.json`
- No `any` — use `unknown` and narrow types
- Define all props with explicit interfaces
- Use `type` for unions, `interface` for object shapes
- All API response types must be defined in `types/`
- Use `satisfies` for config objects to get type checking without widening

---

## Git Workflow

- Branch naming: `feature/<ticket-id>-short-description`, `fix/<ticket-id>-short-description`
- Commit message format: `<type>(<scope>): <description>` (Conventional Commits)
  - Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`, `style`
  - Example: `feat(contact-form): add contact submission form`
- Always update `openspec/specs/api-spec.yml` when API contracts change
- Co-locate component tests next to components or in `__tests__/` mirroring `app/` and `components/`
